{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_013xU9x6EmrhKVt2KYE8JPrD","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Story 10.1: AgentDriver Interface & Types\n2\t\n3\tStatus: verifying\n4\t\n5\t<!-- Note: Validation is optional. Run validate-create-story for quality check before dev-story. -->\n6\t\n7\t## Story\n8\t\n9\tAs a developer,\n10\tI want a formalized AgentDriver interface with DriverHealth, DispatchOpts, and StreamEvent types,\n11\tso that all drivers (Claude Code, Codex, OpenCode) implement a consistent contract and the workflow engine can dispatch to any driver uniformly.\n12\t\n13\t## Acceptance Criteria\n14\t\n15\t1. **Given** the file `src/lib/agents/types.ts`\n16\t   **When** the interface is refactored\n17\t   **Then** `AgentDriver` has these members: `readonly name: string`, `readonly defaultModel: string`, `readonly capabilities: DriverCapabilities`, `healthCheck(): Promise<DriverHealth>`, `dispatch(opts: DispatchOpts): AsyncIterable<StreamEvent>`, `getLastCost(): number | null`\n18\t   **And** each member is typed correctly per the architecture document\n19\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n20\t\n21\t2. **Given** the `DispatchOpts` interface in `src/lib/agents/types.ts`\n22\t   **When** inspected\n23\t   **Then** it includes: `prompt: string`, `model: string`, `cwd: string`, `sourceAccess: boolean`, `plugins?: string[]`, `timeout?: number`, `outputContract?: OutputContract`\n24\t   **And** optional fields use `?` syntax (not `| undefined`)\n25\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n26\t\n27\t3. **Given** the `DriverHealth` interface in `src/lib/agents/types.ts`\n28\t   **When** inspected\n29\t   **Then** it includes: `available: boolean`, `authenticated: boolean`, `version: string | null`, `error?: string`\n30\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n31\t\n32\t4. **Given** the `DriverCapabilities` interface in `src/lib/agents/types.ts`\n33\t   **When** inspected\n34\t   **Then** it includes at minimum: `supportsPlugins: boolean`, `supportsStreaming: boolean`, `costReporting: boolean`\n35\t   **And** the interface is extensible (new boolean fields can be added without breaking existing drivers)\n36\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n37\t\n38\t5. **Given** the `ErrorCategory` type in `src/lib/agents/types.ts`\n39\t   **When** inspected\n40\t   **Then** it is a union of exactly: `'RATE_LIMIT' | 'NETWORK' | 'AUTH' | 'TIMEOUT' | 'UNKNOWN'`\n41\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n42\t\n43\t6. **Given** the `OutputContract` interface in `src/lib/agents/types.ts`\n44\t   **When** inspected\n45\t   **Then** it includes: `version: number`, `taskName: string`, `storyId: string`, `driver: string`, `model: string`, `timestamp: string`, `cost_usd: number | null`, `duration_ms: number`, `changedFiles: string[]`, `testResults: TestResults | null`, `output: string`, `acceptanceCriteria: ACStatus[]`\n46\t   **And** `TestResults` has `passed: number`, `failed: number`, `coverage: number | null`\n47\t   **And** `ACStatus` has `id: string`, `description: string`, `status: string`\n48\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n49\t\n50\t7. **Given** `dispatch()` on the new `AgentDriver` interface\n51\t   **When** its return type is inspected\n52\t   **Then** it returns `AsyncIterable<StreamEvent>` (not `AgentProcess`, not a Promise of array)\n53\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n54\t\n55\t8. **Given** the existing `StreamEvent` types in `src/lib/agents/stream-parser.ts`\n56\t   **When** the refactoring is complete\n57\t   **Then** all existing `StreamEvent` variant types (`ToolStartEvent`, `ToolInputEvent`, `ToolCompleteEvent`, `TextEvent`, `RetryEvent`, `ResultEvent`) are preserved without breaking changes\n58\t   **And** `ResultEvent` gains an optional `cost_usd: number | null` field (in addition to existing `cost: number`) for multi-driver normalization\n59\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n60\t\n61\t9. **Given** the old `AgentDriver` interface shape (`name`, `spawn()`, `parseOutput()`, `getStatusFile()`)\n62\t   **When** code consuming the old interface is inspected\n63\t   **Then** the old `SpawnOpts` type, `AgentProcess` type, and `AgentEvent` type are preserved as deprecated exports with `@deprecated` JSDoc tags\n64\t   **And** `src/lib/agents/index.ts` barrel still re-exports them for backward compatibility\n65\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n66\t\n67\t10. **Given** `npm run build` is executed\n68\t    **When** the build completes\n69\t    **Then** it succeeds with zero TypeScript errors\n70\t    **And** `npm run test:unit` passes with no regressions in existing test suites\n71\t    <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n72\t\n73\t11. **Given** unit tests for the new types in `src/lib/agents/__tests__/types.test.ts`\n74\t    **When** `npm run test:unit` is executed\n75\t    **Then** tests validate: all `AgentDriver` members exist on a mock implementation, `DispatchOpts` accepts all required and optional fields, `DriverHealth` accepts valid health objects, `DriverCapabilities` accepts capability objects, `ErrorCategory` covers exactly 5 values, `OutputContract` accepts valid contracts, `AsyncIterable<StreamEvent>` return type compiles, deprecated types still compile\n76\t    <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n77\t\n78\t## Tasks / Subtasks\n79\t\n80\t- [x] Task 1: Add new types to `src/lib/agents/types.ts` (AC: #1, #2, #3, #4, #5, #6, #7)\n81\t  - [x] Add `DriverHealth` interface\n82\t  - [x] Add `DriverCapabilities` interface\n83\t  - [x] Add `ErrorCategory` type union\n84\t  - [x] Add `DispatchOpts` interface (import `OutputContract` type)\n85\t  - [x] Add `OutputContract`, `TestResults`, `ACStatus` interfaces\n86\t  - [x] Refactor `AgentDriver` interface to new shape: `name`, `defaultModel`, `capabilities`, `healthCheck()`, `dispatch()`, `getLastCost()`\n87\t  - [x] Mark old `SpawnOpts`, `AgentProcess`, `AgentEvent` with `@deprecated` JSDoc\n88\t\n89\t- [x] Task 2: Update `StreamEvent` types in `src/lib/agents/stream-parser.ts` (AC: #8)\n90\t  - [x] Add optional `cost_usd: number | null` field to `ResultEvent` (keep existing `cost: number` for backward compat)\n91\t  - [x] Verify all existing event types are preserved\n92\t\n93\t- [x] Task 3: Update barrel exports in `src/lib/agents/index.ts` (AC: #9)\n94\t  - [x] Export new types: `DriverHealth`, `DriverCapabilities`, `DispatchOpts`, `ErrorCategory`, `OutputContract`, `TestResults`, `ACStatus`\n95\t  - [x] Keep deprecated type exports with `@deprecated` JSDoc comments\n96\t  - [x] Update `getDriver()` stub signature if needed (still throws — factory implementation is story 10-2)\n97\t\n98\t- [x] Task 4: Update unit tests in `src/lib/agents/__tests__/types.test.ts` (AC: #10, #11)\n99\t  - [x] Add test suite for new `AgentDriver` interface shape (mock implementing all members)\n100\t  - [x] Add test for `DispatchOpts` with all required and optional fields\n101\t  - [x] Add test for `DriverHealth` interface\n102\t  - [x] Add test for `DriverCapabilities` interface\n103\t  - [x] Add test for `ErrorCategory` covering all 5 values\n104\t  - [x] Add test for `OutputContract`, `TestResults`, `ACStatus`\n105\t  - [x] Add test proving `dispatch()` returns `AsyncIterable<StreamEvent>`\n106\t  - [x] Preserve and update existing tests for deprecated types\n107\t  - [x] Verify `npm run build` and `npm run test:unit` pass\n108\t\n109\t## Dev Notes\n110\t\n111\t### Architecture Compliance\n112\t\n113\tThis story implements the **AgentDriver Interface Design** from `_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-multi-framework.md` (Decision 1). Key constraints:\n114\t\n115\t- **Interface signature must match exactly** what the architecture specifies (see Decision 1 code block)\n116\t- `dispatch()` returns `AsyncIterable<StreamEvent>` — this is the core design choice enabling both in-process (Agent SDK yields) and CLI-wrapped (stdout parsed to events) drivers\n117\t- Drivers must be stateless between dispatches except for `lastCost`\n118\t- `DriverCapabilities` enables FR37-FR38 (capability matrix and routing hints) in later stories\n119\t\n120\t### Existing Code to Modify\n121\t\n122\t1. **`src/lib/agents/types.ts`** — Current interface: `{ name, spawn(), parseOutput(), getStatusFile() }`. Must be refactored to new shape. Old types must stay as deprecated exports.\n123\t2. **`src/lib/agents/stream-parser.ts`** — Contains `StreamEvent` union and all variant types. Add `cost_usd` to `ResultEvent`. Do NOT change `parseStreamLine()` behavior — it stays Claude-Code-specific. Other drivers will have their own parsers.\n124\t3. **`src/lib/agents/index.ts`** — Barrel file. Must export new types. The `getDriver()` function currently throws — leave that (factory comes in story 10-2).\n125\t4. **`src/lib/agents/__tests__/types.test.ts`** — Existing tests for old interface. Must be updated for new interface AND kept for deprecated types.\n126\t\n127\t### What NOT to Do\n128\t\n129\t- Do NOT create `src/lib/agents/drivers/` directory yet — that is story 10-2 (factory) and 10-3 (claude-code driver extraction)\n130\t- Do NOT modify `workflow-engine.ts` or `agent-dispatch.ts` — integration comes in story 10-5\n131\t- Do NOT create a `model-resolver.ts` — that is story 10-4\n132\t- Do NOT remove the old types — they must stay as deprecated exports for backward compatibility until story 10-3 completes the migration\n133\t- Do NOT change `parseStreamLine()` in `stream-parser.ts` — only extend `ResultEvent` type\n134\t\n135\t### Error Classification (from Architecture)\n136\t\n137\tThe `ErrorCategory` type must use exactly these 5 values, in this priority order for classification:\n138\t1. HTTP 429 or \"rate limit\" in message -> `RATE_LIMIT`\n139\t2. ECONNREFUSED, ETIMEDOUT, ENOTFOUND -> `NETWORK`\n140\t3. HTTP 401/403 or \"unauthorized\"/\"forbidden\" -> `AUTH`\n141\t4. Process killed by timeout -> `TIMEOUT`\n142\t5. Everything else -> `UNKNOWN`\n143\t\n144\tDrivers must NOT invent new categories. This will be enforced via the type system.\n145\t\n146\t### StreamEvent Ordering Contract (from Architecture)\n147\t\n148\tFor reference (implemented in later stories, but types must support):\n149\t1. Zero or more `tool-start` -> `tool-input` -> `tool-complete` sequences\n150\t2. Zero or more `text` events (interleaved)\n151\t3. Zero or more `retry` events\n152\t4. Exactly one `result` event at the end\n153\t\n154\t### Testing Patterns\n155\t\n156\t- Follow existing Vitest patterns in `src/lib/agents/__tests__/types.test.ts`\n157\t- Type-level tests: construct values satisfying each interface to prove they compile\n158\t- Runtime tests: assert field values on constructed objects\n159\t- Use `describe/it/expect` structure consistent with existing test file\n160\t- Do NOT use mocking frameworks — these are pure type/interface tests\n161\t\n162\t### Project Structure Notes\n163\t\n164\t- All new types go in `src/lib/agents/types.ts` (single file, not sharded)\n165\t- `OutputContract` type lives here because it's part of `DispatchOpts` — the separate `output-contract.ts` module (story 10-4+) will import this type\n166\t- No new files created in this story — only modifications to existing files\n167\t\n168\t### References\n169\t\n170\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-multi-framework.md#Decision 1: Driver Interface Design]\n171\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-multi-framework.md#Implementation Patterns & Consistency Rules]\n172\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-multi-framework.md#Story 1.1: AgentDriver Interface & Types]\n173\t- [Source: src/lib/agents/types.ts — current interface to refactor]\n174\t- [Source: src/lib/agents/stream-parser.ts — StreamEvent types to extend]\n175\t\n176\t<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-START:story-verification -->\n177\t## Verification Requirements\n178\t\n179\t- [ ] Showboat proof document created (verification/10-1-agentdriver-interface-types-proof.md)\n180\t- [ ] All acceptance criteria verified with real-world evidence via docker exec\n181\t- [ ] Test coverage meets target (100%)\n182\t\n183\t## Documentation Requirements\n184\t\n185\t- [ ] Relevant AGENTS.md files updated\n186\t- [ ] Exec-plan created in docs/exec-plans/active/10-1-agentdriver-interface-types.md\n187\t\n188\t## Testing Requirements\n189\t\n190\t- [ ] Unit tests written for all new/changed code\n191\t- [ ] Coverage target: 100%\n192\t<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-END:story-verification -->\n193\t\n194\t## Dev Agent Record\n195\t\n196\t### Agent Model Used\n197\t\n198\tClaude Opus 4.6 (1M context)\n199\t\n200\t### Debug Log References\n201\t\n202\tN/A — no debug issues encountered.\n203\t\n204\t### Completion Notes List\n205\t\n206\t- Refactored `AgentDriver` interface to new v2 shape with `dispatch()`, `healthCheck()`, `getLastCost()`, `capabilities`, `defaultModel`\n207\t- Added `DriverHealth`, `DriverCapabilities`, `ErrorCategory`, `DispatchOpts`, `OutputContract`, `TestResults`, `ACStatus` types\n208\t- Marked old `SpawnOpts`, `AgentProcess`, `AgentEvent` as `@deprecated` with JSDoc\n209\t- Extended `ResultEvent` with optional `cost_usd` field\n210\t- Updated barrel exports in `index.ts` with all new types\n211\t- Comprehensive test suite: 30+ tests covering all interfaces, deprecated types, and barrel re-exports\n212\t- Build: zero TS errors in agents module. All 4219 unit tests pass.\n213\t\n214\t### File List\n215\t\n216\t- `src/lib/agents/types.ts` — refactored interface + new types + deprecated old types\n217\t- `src/lib/agents/stream-parser.ts` — added `cost_usd` to `ResultEvent`\n218\t- `src/lib/agents/index.ts` — updated barrel exports\n219\t- `src/lib/agents/__tests__/types.test.ts` — rewritten test suite\n220\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01DJn3zvMdrKyrbtqTXgfYoQ","session_id":"61d40628-eabe-45b5-b544-2f5989944a22","uuid":"071e8a8e-48ff-4eaa-9f96-8e08c3358026","timestamp":"2026-04-03T06:38:57.242Z"}
