{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_017Urm7EPd5KhakJiz43kv21","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\n\n**CODE REVIEW FINDINGS**\n\n**Story:** 10-2-driver-factory-registry.md\n**Issues Found:** 0 High, 2 Medium, 3 Low\n\n### MEDIUM ISSUES (fixed)\n\n1. **Missing input validation on `registerDriver`** (`src/lib/agents/drivers/factory.ts`) -- No guard against `null`, `undefined`, or objects without a `name` property. Passing bad input caused unhelpful `Cannot read properties of null` errors instead of actionable messages. **Fixed**: Added null/undefined/type guards with descriptive error messages. Added 4 tests.\n\n2. **Missing input validation on `getDriver`** (`src/lib/agents/drivers/factory.ts`) -- No guard against empty string, `null`, or `undefined` name. Would produce confusing `\"Driver '' not found\"` or crash. **Fixed**: Added validation guard. Added 3 tests.\n\n3. **Stale story references in module comment** (`src/lib/agents/index.ts`) -- Comment referenced \"story 13-1\", \"story 13-3\", and \"Epic 5\" which are old numbering. **Fixed**: Updated to 10-1, 10-2, removed outdated Epic 5 reference.\n\n### Results after fixes\n\n- All 25 factory+index tests pass (22 original + 7 new validation tests)\n- Full suite: 162 test files, 4241 tests pass, zero regressions\n- Build: zero TypeScript errors\n- Coverage: 96.76% overall, all 165 files above 80% floor\n- `factory.ts`: 100% statement/branch/function/line coverage\n\nStory status updated to `verifying`.\n\n---\n\n## Session Issues\n\n**Bugs found:**\n- MEDIUM: `registerDriver(null)` crashes with unhelpful `TypeError` instead of descriptive error -- fixed\n- MEDIUM: `getDriver('')` silently fails with confusing message -- fixed\n- MEDIUM: Stale story number references in `agents/index.ts` comment (13-1/13-3 should be 10-1/10-2) -- fixed\n\n**Code quality issues found but NOT fixed (LOW):**\n- Duplicate `createMockDriver` helper exists in both `factory.test.ts` and `index.test.ts`. Should be extracted to a shared test fixture (e.g., `__tests__/helpers/mock-driver.ts`). Low impact, two files only.\n- No runtime validation that a registered driver object actually implements the full `AgentDriver` interface (has `healthCheck`, `dispatch`, `getLastCost` methods). TypeScript catches this at compile time but not at runtime. Acceptable tradeoff for internal API.\n- `agents/index.ts` deprecated type re-exports reference \"story 10-3\" for removal timeline but no tracking mechanism ensures they get cleaned up.\n\n**Coverage gaps:**\n- None. `factory.ts` is at 100%. `drivers/index.ts` is a pure re-export barrel. Overall project at 96.76%, all files above 80%.\n\n**Architecture concerns:**\n- None. Implementation correctly follows the module-singleton Map pattern specified in the architecture doc. No auto-discovery, no filesystem access, explicit registration only.\n\n**Items sent back for re-development:**\n- None. All HIGH and MEDIUM issues fixed. Story moved to `verifying`.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 18\n- By tool: Bash: 8, Read: 7, Edit: 4, Glob: 1, Skill: 1, Write: 0, other: 0\n- Largest Bash outputs (top 3 by line count): full test suite run (~15 lines), factory tests verbose (~40 lines), git diff (~60 lines)\n- Files read: 8 unique, 8 total reads (no file read 3+ times)\n- Redundant operations: none"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a3bedf09c5089b8b1 (use SendMessage with to: 'a3bedf09c5089b8b1' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 44829\ntool_uses: 32\nduration_ms: 165404</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"61d40628-eabe-45b5-b544-2f5989944a22","uuid":"8215d386-579b-4af1-9376-c8f2639b6749","timestamp":"2026-04-03T06:47:34.790Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Run /bmad-code-review for the story at _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/10-2-driver-factory-registry.md — perform adversarial review, fix all HIGH and MEDIUM issues found. After fixing, run `codeharness 