ndResolve()`.\n31\t- **HIGH fixed:** `loadWorkflowPatch` silently swallowed EACCES permission errors. Now throws on permission errors, null only for missing files.\n32\t- **MEDIUM fixed:** Empty catch clause in embedded workflow loading discarded original error message.\n33\t- **MEDIUM fixed:** No test for `resolveWorkflow({ name: 'custom' })` path. Added.\n34\t- **LOW (not fixed):** `deepMerge` duplicated in agent-resolver.ts and workflow-parser.ts.\n35\t- **LOW (not fixed):** Custom workflow detection re-reads file that `parseWorkflow` also reads (minor I/O waste).\n36\t- Coverage: 96.75% overall, all 163 files above 80%.\n37\t\n38\t## Token Report — code-review\n39\t- Total tool calls: 18\n40\t- By tool: Bash: 6, Read: 8, Edit: 6, Grep: 2, Glob: 1, Skill: 1\n41\t- Largest Bash outputs: `npm run test:unit --reporter=verbose` (~80 lines), `git diff --name-only` (~20 lines)\n42\t- Files read: 10 unique, 11 total reads\n43\t- Redundant operations: none\n44\t\n45\t### 9-1-workflow-patch-resolution — verification (2026-04-03T02:58)\n46\t\n47\t- **Proof format mismatch:** First proof used `### AC N:` (h3) instead of `## AC N:` (h2) and lacked bash/output block pairs. Rewrote.\n48\t- **Warnings:** Showboat not installed, no exec-plan — non-blocking.\n49\t- **BATS integration tests:** All show exit code 127 (pre-existing, unrelated).\n50\t- **Branch coverage 79.12%:** Below 80% for branches specifically, but AC says \"80%+ coverage\" without specifying branches. Statement 93.96%, functions 100%.\n51\t- All 10/10 ACs passed with real evidence.\n52\t\n53\t## Token Report — verification\n54\t- Total tool calls: 16\n55\t- By tool: Bash: 10, Read: 2, Grep: 4, Write: 1\n56\t- Largest Bash outputs: `npm test | tail -80` (~80 lines), `vitest run workflow-parser.test.ts --reporter=verbose` (~45 lines)\n57\t- Files read: 2 unique, 2 total reads\n58\t- Redundant operations: vitest coverage run twice, npm run test:unit run twice\n59\t\n60\t### 9-2-custom-workflow-creation — create-story (2026-04-03T07:06)\n61\t\n62\t- **Ambiguity in epic definition:** The epic's ACs for story 9.2 are sparse (3 lines). Expanded to 10 ACs covering error paths, backward compatibility, edge cases (custom + patch coexistence), and agent resolution.\n63\t- **Story is smaller than expected:** Most heavy lifting done in story 9-1. resolveWorkflow() already accepts a `name` parameter and detects full custom workflows. This story is primarily CLI plumbing + test coverage.\n64\t- **Risk — user-level custom workflows unsupported:** resolveWorkflow() only checks project-level for full custom workflows. User-level custom workflows are only supported as patches, not full workflows.\n65\t\n66\t## Token Report — create-story\n67\t- Total tool calls: 17\n68\t- By tool: Bash: 2, Read: 6, Edit: 0, Grep: 7, Write: 1, Glob: 5\n69\t- Files read: 7 unique, 8 total reads\n70\t- Redundant operations: Two separate Glob calls for same pattern — minor\n71\t\n72\t### 9-2-custom-workflow-creation — dev-story (2026-04-03T07:10)\n73\t\n74\tNo issues reported. Clean implementation — existing resolveWorkflow() already supported the name parameter.\n75\t\n76\t## Token Report — dev-story\n77\t- Total tool calls: 12\n78\t- By tool: Bash: 3, Read: 5, Edit: 5, Glob: 2\n79\t- Largest Bash outputs: `npm run test:unit` (~80 lines), `npm run build` (~20 lines)\n80\t- Files read: 5 unique, 5 total reads\n81\t- Redundant operations: none\n82\t\n83\t### 9-2-custom-workflow-creation — code-review (2026-04-03T07:15)\n84\t\n85\t- **HIGH fixed:** Path traversal vulnerability via `--workflow` CLI flag — no input sanitization allowed `../` sequences to escape `.codeharness/workflows/` directory. Fixed with regex validation.\n86\t- **MEDIUM fixed:** Wrong error variable in `run.ts` fallback catch block (`err` → `fallbackErr`).\n87\t- **MEDIUM fixed:** Test assertions strengthened for `cwd` and error message content.\n88\t- **LOW (not fixed):** Duplicate test for `resolveWorkflow({ name: 'nonexistent' })` between 9