{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01KrC9w5nenM7mJDRJ3Pqqo4","type":"tool_result","content":"100\t2. **Code review catching real bugs:** 3 HIGH severity bugs caught (path traversal, data loss, input validation). These would have been production defects.\n101\t3. **Epic 4 completed:** All 4 stories (agent dispatch, session management, trace IDs, source isolation) shipped and verified.\n102\t4. **Test quality:** 100% coverage on both trace-id.ts and source-isolation.ts modules. 31 tests written for 5-1 in dev phase alone.\n103\t5. **Zero retries this session:** All stories completed on first attempt — no stuck/failed cycles.\n104\t6. **Session issues log is working:** Subagent self-reporting produced actionable data for this retro.\n105\t\n106\t---\n107\t\n108\t## 5. What Went Wrong\n109\t\n110\t1. **Time budget exhaustion:** Story 5-1 got through dev but couldn't complete code-review or verify. It's stuck at \"review\" status — needs manual follow-up.\n111\t2. **`codeharness verify` is unreliable:** Fails on harness state flags that aren't set during subagent runs. This forced manual verification workarounds in both 4-3 and 4-4.\n112\t3. **AGENTS.md documentation debt:** 5 new modules have no AGENTS.md entries. The verify command flags this every time, burning cycles on a known-stale doc.\n113\t4. **Cost report stale:** `codeharness stats --save` requires `session-logs/` directory which doesn't exist for this session type. The cost report only covers the prior session's data.\n114\t5. **Sprint state file divergence:** `ralph/.state-snapshot.json` shows 4-4 as \"verifying\" and 5-1 as \"backlog\" — but sprint-status.yaml shows 4-4 as done and 5-1 as review. State files are out of sync.\n115\t\n116\t---\n117\t\n118\t## 6. Lessons Learned\n119\t\n120\t### Patterns to Repeat\n121\t\n122\t- **Code review as a mandatory gate:** Every HIGH bug this session was caught by code review, not tests. The adversarial review phase is load-bearing.\n123\t- **Session issues log:** Self-reported token data from subagents made cost analysis possible without working harness stats.\n124\t- **Pure-logic module design:** Both trace-id and source-isolation achieved 100% coverage because they have no I/O dependencies. This pattern works.\n125\t\n126\t### Patterns to Avoid\n127\t\n128\t- **Running `codeharness verify` without checking preconditions:** Wastes a full invocation cycle. Either fix the verify command or skip it when flags aren't set.\n129\t- **Running coverage twice:** Once is enough. The second targeted run is redundant when the first already reports per-file coverage.\n130\t- **Starting a new story late in a session:** 5-1 was started knowing time was short. It would have been cleaner to stop after Epic 4 closure.\n131\t\n132\t---\n133\t\n134\t## 7. Action Items\n135\t\n136\t| # | Action | Priority | Owner |\n137\t|---|--------|----------|-------|\n138\t| 1 | Complete code-review and verify for story 5-1 | HIGH | Next session |\n139\t| 2 | Fix `codeharness verify` to work without pre-set harness state flags | MEDIUM | Backlog |\n140\t| 3 | Update `src/lib/AGENTS.md` with entries for agent-dispatch, agent-resolver, session-manager, trace-id, source-isolation modules | MEDIUM | Next session |\n141\t| 4 | Fix `codeharness stats --save` to work for non-ralph sessions | LOW | Backlog |\n142\t| 5 | Sync `ralph/.state-snapshot.json` with `sprint-state.json` | LOW | Next session |\n143\t| 6 | Fix pre-existing TS errors in `src/commands/__tests__/run.test.ts` | LOW | Backlog |\n144\t| 7 | Address deferred LOW issues from 4-3 and 4-4 code reviews | LOW | Backlog |\n145\t\n146\t---\n147\t\n148\t# Session Retrospective — 2026-04-03 (Session 2)\n149\t\n150\t**Timestamp:** 2026-04-03T02:00Z\n151\t**Session window:** ~2026-04-03T01:53 to ~2026-04-03T02:15 (approx. 22 minutes)\n152\t**Sprint progress:** 15/28 stories done (53.6%), Epics 1-4 complete, Epic 5 started\n153\t\n154\t---\n155\t\n156\t## 1. Session Summary\n157\t\n158\tThis session picked up story 5-1-flow-execution-sequential-steps at `review` status and drove it to `done`. No new stories were started.\n159\t\n160\t| Story | Phases Run | Outcome | Notes |\n161\t|-------|-----------|---------|-------|\n162\t| 5-1-flow-execution-sequential-steps | code-review, verification, proof-doc fix, AGENTS.md update | **Done** | 14/14 ACs verified. Commit `b983273`. |\n163\t\n164\t**Activities completed:**\n165\t1. Code review found 2 HIGH bugs and 2 MEDIUM issues — all fixed\n166\t2. Test-provable verification: 14/14 ACs passed, 3963 tests green, 99.2% stmt coverage on workflow-engine.ts\n167\t3. Proof document formatting fix (needed `**Tier:**` bold format)\n168\t4. `src/lib/AGENTS.md` updated to include `source-isolation.ts` and `workflow-engine.ts`\n169\t\n170\t---\n171\t\n172\t## 2. Issues Analysis\n173\t\n174\t### Bugs Found by Code Review (fixed)\n175\t\n176\t| Severity | Issue |\n177\t|----------|-------|\n178\t| HIGH | Per-story RATE_LIMIT/NETWORK/SDK_INIT errors did not halt the outer flow loop — only the inner work-items loop. Catastrophic failures would be silently swallowed. |\n179\t| HIGH | Dispatch failures did not record a TaskCheckpoint in workflow state, violating AC #13. Crash recovery would lose track of failed tasks. |\n180\t| MEDIUM | Coverage gaps — 8 new tests added. Coverage improved to 99.2% stmt / 87% branch. |\n181\t\n182\t### LOW Issues Deferred (not fixed)\n183\t\n184\t- Duplicate checkpoint creation logic in `dispatchTask` else branch\n185\t- `handleDispatchError` and `recordErrorInState` could be merged\n186\t- `warn()` calls for skipped tasks don't propagate to `EngineResult.errors`\n187\t- Branch coverage at 87% — remaining uncovered branches are defensive null checks on YAML parse results\n188\t- No integration test verifying actual YAML parsing (all YAML mocked)\n189\t\n190\t### Infrastructure Issues\n191\t\n192\t- **AGENTS.md was stale** — missing entries for `source-isolation.ts` and `workflow-engine.ts`. Fixed in this session.\n193\t- **Prior action item resolved:** Action item #1 from Session 1 (\"Complete code-review and verify for story 5-1\") is now done.\n194\t- **Prior action item resolved:** Action item #3 from Session 1 (\"Update AGENTS.md\") is now partially addressed (2 of 5 missing modules added).\n195\t\n196\t---\n197\t\n198\t## 3. Cost Analysis\n199\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_011dPfV5dJvidkjzxNw7eopH","session_id":"61d40628-eabe-45b5-b544-2f5989944a22","uuid":"a36cfb79-bc0e-462a-a7ad-4028d67babdb","timestamp":"2026-04-03T06:53:40.967Z"}
